  "beats": [
    {
      "beat_id": "B01",
      "act": "HOOK",
      "narration_text": "Namaste. Liam, in for Bear. Hydrogen's two-p state decays in about a nanosecond, while two-s survives roughly a tenth of a second: almost eight orders of magnitude longer. The energy gap exists, but the fastest radiative channel is forbidden.",
