        "at": "2026-07-18T18:55:34"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B02",
      "act": "FAST DECAY",
      "narration_text": "Allowed electric-dipole transitions in hydrogen commonly occur on nanosecond scales. The two-p to one-s transition is the nearby benchmark.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "manim"
      },
      "estimated_duration_s": 10,
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B02.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 9.47,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B02.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T18:55:34"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B03",
      "act": "SLOW STATE",
      "narration_text": "The two-s state lies about ten point two electron volts above one-s, yet its lifetime in isolated hydrogen is about zero point one two seconds. It is metastable, not permanently stable.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "manim"
      },
      "estimated_duration_s": 13,
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B03.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 12.12,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B03.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T18:55:34"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B04",
      "act": "QUESTION",
      "narration_text": "Why can two-s not simply emit one photon and fall to one-s? Energy conservation allows the photon energy. The transition amplitude is blocked by symmetry and angular-momentum selection rules.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "manim"
      },
      "estimated_duration_s": 13,
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B04.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 12.05,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B04.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T18:55:34"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B05",
      "act": "NAIVE",
      "narration_text": "An energy gap is necessary for spontaneous emission, but not sufficient. The electromagnetic interaction's leading electric-dipole matrix element must also connect the initial and final states.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "manim"
      },
      "estimated_duration_s": 13,
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B05.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 11.82,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B05.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T18:55:34"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B06",
      "act": "E1 RULE",
      "narration_text": "For an electric-dipole, or E-one, transition, the orbital selection rule is delta ell equals plus or minus one, with a parity change. This is the dominant single-photon channel for ordinary atomic decays.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "manim"
      },
      "estimated_duration_s": 14,
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B06.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 12.82,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B06.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T18:55:34"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B07",
      "act": "FORBIDDEN",
      "narration_text": "Both two-s and one-s have ell zero and even parity. Their delta ell is zero, so the electric-dipole matrix element vanishes. The two-s to one-s E-one transition is forbidden.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "manim"
      },
      "estimated_duration_s": 14,
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B07.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 11.09,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B07.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T18:55:34"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B08",
      "act": "COMPARE",
      "narration_text": "Two-p has ell one and odd parity. Falling to one-s gives delta ell minus one and changes parity, so the E-one channel is allowed. Two-s fails both E-one signatures.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "manim"
      },
      "estimated_duration_s": 13,
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B08.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 10.54,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B08.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T18:55:34"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B09",
      "act": "TWO PHOTONS",
      "narration_text": "Two-s escapes mainly through simultaneous two-photon emission via intermediate virtual states. The combined two-photon angular momentum and parity can satisfy the total transition rules. The second-order process is much slower than one-photon E-one emission.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "manim"
      },
      "estimated_duration_s": 16,
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B09.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 15.74,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B09.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T18:55:34"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B10",
      "act": "USE",
      "narration_text": "That long lifetime makes two-s useful for precision spectroscopy. The one-s to two-s transition can be driven by two photons, enabling exceptionally narrow and precise hydrogen measurements.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "manim"
      },
      "estimated_duration_s": 13,
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B10.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 11.86,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B10.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T18:55:34"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B11",
      "act": "SCOPE",
      "narration_text": "Forbidden does not mean impossible. It means forbidden in a specified approximation or multipole channel. Here the leading one-photon electric-dipole route vanishes, while the two-photon route remains.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "manim"
      },
      "estimated_duration_s": 14,
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B11.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 12.14,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B11.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T18:55:34"
      }
    },
    {
      "beat_id": "B12",
      "act": "YOUR TURN",
      "narration_text": "Your turn. Compare two-p to one-s and two-s to one-s. Which has delta ell plus or minus one and a parity change? Two-p to one-s, so it is E-one allowed.",
      "shot": {
        "type": "manim"
      },
      "estimated_duration_s": 13,
      "audio_file": "mp3/beat-B12.mp3",
      "actual_duration_s": 9.24,
      "build": {
        "status": "MANIM",
        "src": "manim/B12.mp4",
        "filled_by": "manim",
        "at": "2026-07-18T18:55:34"
      }
    },
